/*
There are three types of control statements
1. Conditional branching
2. Conditional looping
3. Conditional jumping

Conditional branching : All conditional branching statements are used to control the flow of a program
Five types of Conditional branching statements
1. simple if
2. if else
3. nested if else
4. if else ladder
5. switch case

Syntax for Conditional branching statements:

1. simple if :

if(condition)
           executable statement;

2. if else :
In if else we have two choices to choose : if-'true' case ; else-'false' case

if(condition)
           statement 1;
else
           statement 2;


*/
